{"title":"How to lock/unlock the Recently Deleted and Hidden albums in Photos","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/2404133/how-to-lock-recently-deleted-hidden-albums-photos.html","date":1722589200000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>What’s the point of hiding media in the Photos app if other people with access to your device can see it? That seemed to be the point of Apple’s upgrade to Photos in iOS 16, iPadOS 16, and macOS 13 Ventura. By default, any items you chose to hide in your library and your Recently Delete album would require Touch ID, Face ID, or a device/account password to view.</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?w=1200\" alt=\"macOS Photos Hidden Recently Deleted settings\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1204w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=300%2C273&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=768%2C698&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=1200%2C1090&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1090\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<figcaption><p> Use Photos Settings in macOS to disable the lock option for the Hidden and Recently Deleted albums.</p></figcaption>\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"macOS Photos Hidden Recently Deleted settings\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1204w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=300%2C273&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=768%2C698&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=1200%2C1090&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1090\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p> Use Photos Settings in macOS to disable the lock option for the Hidden and Recently Deleted albums.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"macOS Photos Hidden Recently Deleted settings\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1204w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=300%2C273&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=768%2C698&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-option-mac-bordered.png?resize=1200%2C1090&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1090\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p> Use Photos Settings in macOS to disable the lock option for the Hidden and Recently Deleted albums.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div></div>\n\t\t</div></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p>If you let your kids, roommates, parents, or others have access to the same Mac account or sometimes hand your phone to someone without supervising it, the locked protection on those albums is a plus. However, if you’re a solo operator of your own hardware, you can disable this feature.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Photos for macOS, choose <em>Photos &gt; Settings &gt; General</em> and uncheck, <em>Use Touch ID or password.</em> In iOS/iPadOS, go to <em>Settings</em> &gt; <em>Photos</em> and disable <em>Use Touch ID/Face ID</em>.</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?w=1014\" alt=\"iOS hide photos\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1183w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=254%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 254w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=768%2C909&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=1014%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1014w\" width=\"1014\" height=\"1200\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<figcaption><p>Select one or more images, and you can then choose to Hide (or Unhide) them.</p></figcaption>\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"iOS hide photos\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1183w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=254%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 254w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=768%2C909&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=1014%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1014w\" width=\"1014\" height=\"1200\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p>Select one or more images, and you can then choose to Hide (or Unhide) them.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"iOS hide photos\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1183w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=254%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 254w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=768%2C909&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hide-photos-ios-bordered.png?resize=1014%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1014w\" width=\"1014\" height=\"1200\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p>Select one or more images, and you can then choose to Hide (or Unhide) them.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div></div>\n\t\t</div></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re wondering where the Hidden album is, by the way, it’s…hidden:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>In macOS, choose <em>View &gt; Show Hidden Photo Album</em> to reveal it in the sidebar. You can hide or unhide media by selecting one or more items first and Control-clicking or right-clicking them, or by first selecting multiple and choosing Hide or Unhide <em>number</em> <em>Photo/Video/Item(s)</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>In iOS/iPadOS, go to <em>Settings</em> &gt; <em>Photos</em> and enable <em>Show Hidden Album</em>. To hide or unhide an image or video in the Photos album, tap it and then tap the More (…) button in the upper-right corner, and tap <em>Hide</em> or <em>Unhide</em>. You can also tap <em>Select</em> in an album or gallery view, select multiple items, then tap the More (…) button in the lower-right corner and, likewise, tap <em>Hide</em> or <em>Unhide</em>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?w=1200\" alt=\"macOS Photos Hidden album\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1682w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=300%2C103&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=768%2C264&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=1200%2C412&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=1536%2C528&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"412\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<figcaption><p>The hidden Hidden album in Photos for Mac, revealed.</p></figcaption>\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"macOS Photos Hidden album\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1682w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=300%2C103&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=768%2C264&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=1200%2C412&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=1536%2C528&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"412\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p>The hidden Hidden album in Photos for Mac, revealed.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"macOS Photos Hidden album\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1682w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=300%2C103&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=768%2C264&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=1200%2C412&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-hidden-photos-album-mac-bordered.png?resize=1536%2C528&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"412\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p>The hidden Hidden album in Photos for Mac, revealed.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div></div>\n\t\t</div></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p><em>This Mac 911 article is in response to a question submitted by Macworld reader Cynthia.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ask Mac 911</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve compiled a list of the questions we get asked most frequently, along with answers and links to columns: <a href=\"http://www.macworld.com/article/3077986/os-x/your-top-questions-to-mac-911-and-some-answers.html\">read our super FAQ</a> to see if your question is covered. If not, we’re always looking for new problems to solve! Email yours to <a href=\"mailto:mac911@macworld.com\">mac911@macworld.com</a>, including screen captures as appropriate and whether you want your full name used. Not every question will be answered; we don’t reply to emails, and we cannot provide direct troubleshooting advice.</p>\n\n</div>","author":"","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"f335e2ca263ce096fde36cc8681c2e06ad0f98020f48862bbbe7573765e2405a","category":"Apple"}